--- !u!114 &8976732511323470768
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 6664043339550924468}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: fbeb6d65be27d3b40a131a1e4ace56b5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  steps:
  - message: "Hi again, Gizmo! The desert\u2019s quiet... feels like it\u2019s waiting
      for something big."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 1
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "It\u2019s waiting for you, {player}. This is the perfect field for
      your first motion test."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 1
    endTime: 2
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Another challenge already? What\u2019s the focus this time, Gizmo?"
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Rectilinear motion\u2014movement in a straight line. Think of it as
      your foundation for everything ahead."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 1
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "So we\u2019re talking about straight-line travel, right?"
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 1
    endTime: 2
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Exactly! Imagine your hovercraft gliding perfectly forward across this
      sand\u2014no turns, just a smooth path."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Sounds simple enough. But what exactly are we measuring?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Distance and Displacement. Distance is how long the path has taken.
      Displacement is the distance between the start point and destination.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 4
    endTime: 5
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: So, if I circle back to where I started, my distance is large but my
      displacement is zero?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 5
    endTime: 7
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Right on the mark! Now, let\u2019s add motion details\u2014speed and
      velocity."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 7
    endTime: 8
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Speed means how fast I move, like distance divided by time?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 11
    endTime: 12
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Correct. Speed is the scalar quantity defined as the total distance
      covered per unit time.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 12
    endTime: 13
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: And velocity is different because it includes direction?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 14
    endTime: 15
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Exactly! Velocity is the measured speed between two specified points.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 14
    endTime: 15
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: You can look at the guidebooks and check for more details!
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 15
    endTime: 16
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Okay and acceleration comes in when my velocity changes?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 17
    endTime: 18
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Yes. Acceleration is the change in velocity per unit time, meaning it
      shows how fast the object moves.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 18
    endTime: 19
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Makes sense. Straight path, changing speed\u2026 I can visualize it
      now. Thanks to the guidebook!"
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 19
    endTime: 20
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Welcome {player}, now let's get your understanding tested with a quiz!
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 19
    endTime: 20
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
